• Credit Rating Reaffirmations:

  • Key Supporting Factors:

  • Operational/product diversity, high asset ownership/operator status, stable gas/LNG contracts (CPI-linked).

Material Information Summary (Asset Sale Announcement):

  • Non-dilutive cash raised: AUD $8 million (US$5M) from sale of Big Sandy Lithium Project and Lithium Research Center.
  • Buyer: Subsidiaries of NTEC (AZL’s largest shareholder).
  • Strategic focus: Proceeds directed to development of Prairie Lithium Project (Phase 1 production approved).
  • Key implication: AZL exits Big Sandy due to regulatory hurdles, streamlining capital allocation to near-term production asset (Prairie).
  • Additional context: Follows oversubscribed AUD $4.25M SPP; no shareholder approval required for sale.

Omitted: Operational details of Prairie, historical background, management commentary.

• Substantial Holder Change: Jencay Capital Pty Limited increased its stake in MedAdvisor Limited (MDR) from 7.24% to 8.39%.
  • Shares Acquired: Purchased 9,142,870 ordinary shares for $588,676.58 between 09/04/2025 and 07/07/2025.
  • Current Holding: 52,389,949 ordinary shares held via JP Morgan Nominees Australia Ltd (discretionary investment mandate).

No other material capital markets or liquidity impacts identified.

• Drilling permits received for Horse Heaven Project (Idaho, USA); Phase 1 drilling (up to 20 holes, ~20,000 feet) to commence August 2025, targeting Golden Gate area.
  • Acquisition condition completed: Vendor exercised option to acquire 100% of Horse Heaven Project owner; remaining conditions are due diligence and shareholder approval (GM: 25 July 2025).
  • Escrow release: 12.5M shares to be released 17 July 2025 (early); 5M RMLOC options released 31 July 2025; 81.96M RMLO options expire 31 July 2025.

Material catalyst: Drilling commencement and GM outcome could impact valuation.

Material Information Summary (ASX Announcement – Exploration Update)

  • Exploration Activity Commenced – Initial fieldwork (mapping/sampling) underway at Francis Creek prospect (part of Sybil Project, 100% owned by Sunshine Metals).
  • Key Observations – Vein textures and geochemistry indicate potential for a thicker, higher-grade "boiling zone" extending east/southeast.
  • Historic High-Grade Samples – Rock chips at Francis Creek graded up to 907g/t Au and 262g/t Au; new samples submitted for assay.
  • Drilling Planned – RC drilling scheduled for July–August 2025 at Francis Creek East and Burdekin Veins.
  • Regional Analogue – Sybil shares geological similarities with the Pajingo deposit (4Moz Au produced).

No capital raising, financial data, or material operational changes disclosed.

Material Information Summary (Exploration Update):

  • Exploration Findings:
  • Field mapping confirms upper levels of a copper porphyry system at surface, supporting potential mineralization at depth.
  • Key alteration zones (argillic, silicification) and oxide-after-sulphide veins observed.

  • Historic drillhole re-logging aligns with porphyry system hypothesis.

  • Next Steps:

  • Geophysical reprocessing (MAG, IP, MT) underway; results expected within weeks.

  • Phase I drilling planned for Q4 2025; contractor tendering in progress.

  • JV Context:

  • FMR holds earn-in right to 60% of Southern Porphyry JV (Chile). Target area has 6km corridor of copper-gold-molybdenum potential.

  • Historic Drill Results:

  • Highlight: Drillhole 22LHRC024 intersects 5m @ 0.48% CuEq (0.37% Cu, 0.15g/t Au).
  • Full data tables in appendices.

No material financial/data discrepancies identified.

  • Material Asset Note: LKO's Wombat Gas Field holds 2C resource of 329Bcf, positioning it for East Coast gas supply opportunities.

Material Information Summary:

  • Drilling Program Update:
  • Extension of drilling program at Amadee Prospect, part of the Bousquet Gold Project (Quebec, Canada).
  • Amadee exhibits similar geology to high-grade Paquin Prospect, including smoky quartz veins with historical intercepts of 1.52m @ 6.8g/t Au.

  • Current drilling aims to test potential >1km mineralized strike linking Amadee and Paquin.

  • Upcoming Catalysts:

  • First assay results expected mid-July 2025 from the ongoing drill program.

  • Historical Highlights:

  • Amadee’s mineralization spans >200m strike length, with surface samples up to 8.0g/t Au (channel sampling).

  • Paquin Trend (hosting both prospects) has recorded visible gold in recent drilling (ASX: 24 June 2025).

  • Next Steps:

  • Three additional drillholes planned at Amadee to test western extension of mineralization.

No material capital, operational, or financial updates disclosed; focus remains on exploration progress.

• Final regulatory approvals secured for drilling at Wombat-5 well (Gippsland, Victoria), with no remaining obstacles.
  • Drilling timeline: Condor Rig #1 mobilisation mid-July; spud date 31 July 2025; site prep nearing completion.
  • Resource potential: Wombat-5 targets upper Strzelecki Formation with 10 TJ/day gas potential (independently assessed).
  • Contingent resources: Combined 719 PJ (2C) across Wombat (329 PJ) and Trifon-Gangell (390 PJ) fields.
  • Strategic impact: Successful drilling could support near-term gas supply to Victoria (potential 20 PJ/year for 20 years), addressing forecast shortages from 2026.

Omitted: Site photo, director quotes, detailed pricing conversions, repetitive background.

Material Information Summary

Key Highlights (Resource Upgrade Announcement)

  • Resource Upgrade:
  • Total 151,000 oz Au and 902,000 oz Ag at 1.40 g/t Au and 8.4 g/t Ag, across 3.3Mt.
    • Indicated: 2.2Mt @ 1.40 g/t Au, 9.7 g/t Ag (67% of total).
    • Inferred: 1.1Mt @ 1.54 g/t Au, 6.6 g/t Ag.

  • 16% increase in gold resource vs. prior estimate.

  • Exploration Upside: Mineralization remains open along strike and at depth, with drilling planned to expand resources.

  • Strategic Impact:

  • Bolsters QMines’ hub-and-spoke production model in Central Queensland.
  • Combined JORC resources now ~20Mt across three 100%-owned projects.

Operational Context

  • Mt. Mackenzie will feed into the Mt. Chalmers processing plant (140km away), improving project economics.

Forward-Looking Notes

  • No immediate capital-raising or trading halt declared. Focus on resource growth and integration into mine planning.

Conclusion: Material for valuation due to increased resource scale, higher confidence (Indicated category dominance), and strategic synergies with existing assets.

Omitted: Geological details, drilling methods, JORC compliance, and non-material operational updates.
